-- Ford Motor Plans to Cut Stake in Mazda Under Sumitomo Pact, Nikkei Reports
-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 2010-10-15T17:36:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/ford-motor-plans-to-cut-stake-in-mazda-under-sumitomo-pact-nikkei-reports.html
Ford Motor Co. intends to cut its
stake in Mazda Motor Corp. to 3 percent or less from about 11
percent through selling shares to Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corp.,
Sumitomo Corp. and other companies, Nikkei English News said,
without citing anyone.  Ford holds about 195 million Mazda shares valued at about
42 billion yen ($517 million), according to the report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Chang at 
 gchang1@bloomberg.net  